HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 184
By McKenzie
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Knoxville Alumnae
Chapter of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc.,
upon the occasion of its 112th Founders Day
Celebration.
WHEREAS, it is our privilege to recognize those august organizations that are devoted
to the betterment of their communities as they celebrate milestones in their histories; and
WHEREAS, one such organization is the Knoxville Alumnae Chapter of Delta Sigma
Theta Sorority, Inc., which is hosting its 112th Founders Day Celebration; and
WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc., was founded on January 13, 1913, by
twenty-two undergraduate African-American women at Howard University who wanted to use
their collective strength to promote academic excellence and provide assistance to persons in
need; and
WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc., is a private nonprofit organization whose
purpose is to provide assistance and support in local communities through established
programs; and
WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc., a sisterhood of predominantly Black
college-educated women committed to public service with a focus on the Black community,
continues to make significant efforts to confront the challenges of African Americans and,
hence, all Americans; and
WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc., has distinguished itself as an international
public service organization with a Five-Point programmatic thrust that addresses Economic
Development, Educational Development, International Awareness and Involvement, Physical
and Mental Health, and Political Awareness and Involvement/Social Action; and
