WHEREAS, the Knoxville Alumnae Chapter of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc., serves
the Knoxville community with an active membership that provides services to this community in
each of the programmatic thrusts, including annual college scholarships; and
WHEREAS, the Knoxville Alumnae Chapter of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc., will host
a private Founders Day Celebration on February 22, 2025, in celebration of the sorority's 112th
anniversary, bringing their sisters and community residents together under the theme of "One
Team, One Dream: Honoring the Past, Building the Future"; and
WHEREAS, it is proper that we honor and congratulate this venerable sorority for its
dedication to academic excellence and public service on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the Knoxville Alumnae Chapter of Delta Sigma
Theta Sorority, Inc., upon the occasion of its 112th Founders Day Celebration and commend its
members for their dedication and commitment to educational excellence and public service in
their community.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
